t and hopefully get other opinions. This should probably be in the general section but this is a chance to vent a bit about likes/dislikes in EQ.<br><br>Something that has bugged me since I first started playing EQ is the &quot;uber mobs&quot;. I like to read novels (mostly fantasy with a little si-fi thrown in) and have yet to &quot;see&quot; any character in a story say &quot;I have to round up 50 other heros to be able to defeat this monster&quot;. Isnt it the other way around? Isnt it usually the hero that faces the hordes of demons and somehow overcomes the overwhelming odds pitted against him/her ?<br><br>I also agree about the mob xp. If you help kill a mob should'nt you get some xp? Like on dragon raids, when the mob falls should not everyone involved get a bit of xp? I know that would be hard to implement (maybe impossible) but isnt that what is fair to all that spend the time to help? <br><br>The risk-vs-reward in EQ is very poorly executed. I believe that a good way to solve this problem would be to somehow make it so that the loot was based on your character's level and class. Not sure exactly how this could be done (&lt;---- not a computer wiz by any means). What I mean by this is that if your character solo's a mob could the game not read your characters information and give loot based upon what it read?<br>Maybe the higher lvl your character was the more % chance you had of getting XXX type gear?<br><br>These are just some of my opinions and I would love to see some of your thoughts and comments on what you think could make EQ a much better game.<br><br>Volstagg Iceheart<br>Shaman of Norrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umaximusfaticus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maximus Faticus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/8/02 7:20:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub