sing it as they die.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Nobell hit the nail right on the head. I've spent days of RL time raiding (combined, of course). When my guild was a big ticket on the server and we could raid pretty much exclusively, we'd set up a KS group... which was a combination of high damage dealers and the lowest level characters in the guild. We did it simply to help out the lower levels... the guild was more concerned with the gear and loot that dropped on said raids.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> There is nothing wrong with the &quot;Utopian&quot; idea of everyone participating getting a fare share of the experience from the encounter.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>There is if it f#cks the game mechanics for the other 95% of the game.<br><br>Rara <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubrechtbertolt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brecht Bertolt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 669<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/10/02 10:54:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3399.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ideas, opinions, and BS</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you have to worry about a few tiny pixels of experiance on raid then you shouldn't be raiding ...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Correction. Once one a PoG raid I received two yellow bubles when I was level 52. <p>Brecht Bertolt <BR>Bard of the 54th song <BR>Vivix Protectorate<BR>Retired Officer<BR>"Fire Fighters Don't Die, They go to Hell and re-group!"<img src="http://boddkin.20megsfree.com/images/brechtnewsig1.jpg" border="0"></a> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6634>My Gear</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucarathosollathir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carathos Ollathir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalRainbow.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1724<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/11/02 9:11:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3399.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ideas, opinions, and BS</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you had ever spent time raiding then you would understand that its all about 1 group getting all the exp and the rest getting none or losing it as they die<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>*makes a game show buzzer noise* WRONG!  If YOU had ever spent any time raiding, then you would know that raiding is NOT about getting exp at all.  It's about facing a new challenge or facing an old challenge to get you and your friends nicer gear.  If you want exp, go join a group in OS or Velk's or wherever.  If you want to raid, forget about exp.  Even if they wanted to spread out the exp to all involved in a raid, do you really think you'd see a significant difference?  No.  Exp spread out over a group of 6 is one thing.  Exp spread out over a group of 30 or 40 is quite another.  If you've been playing the game for more than 5 minutes then you KNOW that Verant is not going to give you the best of both worlds. <p>Carathos Ollathir<br>60th level druid<br>Retired</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uwyvernwyrmsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyvern Wyrmsong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/11/02 10:15:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3399.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ideas, opinions, and BS</span><hr size=1> Consider what would happen if semi-uber mobs gave a *proper* amount of experience to all folks that should normally raid that mob.  <br><br>Gorenaire for e.g. - a great fight for people in the mid 50's.  She drops average to below gear for most level 60s that raid serious mobs.  The people in their 50's will need 24+ to kill her, so you gear her experience to adequately reward 24 level 54's.  <br><br>She is a dragon, she has breath AE weapons, slow and freezing blast, complete healing abilities, and respectable melee.  Add that is level 60 and you have a formidable mob if you applied experience bonuses by ability.<br><br>Consider if Gorenaire gave noticeable experience as a reward, say one gold bubble to each of the 24+ level 54's expected in a &quot;normal&quot; raid force and level.  <br><br>The problem is, AA experience is about the same as level 54 experience if memory serves me. (Someone can correct me if I am wrong)  4 level 60 wizards with mana burn can kill Gorenaire with one shot now.  The result is, 4 wizards gather up and nuke Gore for about 1 AA point.<br><br>That is my concern about allowing extra experience for special raid mobs, and allowing a noticeable experience reward to be shared over a whole raid.  It would cause endless bottom feeding by overequipped players nuking lower level raid mobs seeking faster AA experience. <br><br>Sorry I do not have any great solution to go with my criticism except to leave risk and reward based upon the better loot dropping from 0 experience raid mobs.  Raid type mobs die fast enough without adding experience incentives to them.<br><br>Legynd's proposal about small experience bonuses to makeup for tougher non-loot mobs of the same level has some merit, and VI addresses this *slightly* with Zone Experience Modifiers, though these do not completely even out the experience problems. <p>Wyvern Wyrmsong <br>60 Virtuoso<br><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10641">Magelo Character Profile </A> <br><A href="http://pub37.ezboard.com/bmidnightfury">Midnight Fury</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ughie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/11/02 1:48:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3399.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ideas, opinions, and BS</span><hr size=1> I have read alot of novels and seen alot of movies where the hero tries to take on the big bad boss alone and fails only to return later with hoardes of friends to overwhelm the big baddie.<br><br>Most good novels have several heros who each play a role in the final victory.<br><br>If you want the single hero scenerio, you are playing the wrong game.<br><br>Its also a supply and demand economy on the hero side. If boss mobs could all be taken out by a small group, there would be fewer demand for heros. Either Verant would have to significantly increase the number of boss mobs(not likely since worthwhile boss mobs take time and resources) or decrease the number of heroes by charging more for the game. (Legends server)<br><br>But, everquest is primarily a social game. We play to interact with other people. That is what keeps us playing above anything else. Verant knows this and they therefore develop encounters which promote the larger, stronger social structures.<br><br>If you want to be the one hero or small band overcoming overwhelming odds, play Dungeon Seige.<br><br>If you want to have fun with your friends, play EQ.<br><br> <p>GVirtuoso...so much more than just the seventh letter of the alphabet.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utreage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Treage</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>A Cleric_01</span><br>  Posts: 293<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/12/02 7:02:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3399.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ideas, opinions, and BS</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If YOU had ever spent any time raiding, then you would know that raiding is NOT about getting exp at all. It's about facing a new challenge or facing an old challenge to get you and your friends nicer gear.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Thank you for pointing this out, I knew I forgot to put my dog-earred disclaimer in there stating this. If I had a plat for everytime I typed thoses exact same words then I may have a horse by now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I have spent 3-5 days a week raiding for the last 1.5 years, so I somewhat understand how the system works. Recently I've been playing my warrior on raids and have been enjoying being a part of